  "body": [
    "Bhai Karnail Singh Dhiraj is blessed with a melodious voice which never fails to captivate the listener. Bhai Karnail Singh Ji learned Kirtan in the Vidhyala of Gurdwara Bala Sahib, New Delhi from Ustad Bhai Santa Singh Kanwal. At the same time he also received Gurbani Paath Santhya from Giani Harbhajan Singh Ji and Giani Hem Singh Ji. This Vidhyala was run by the Delhi Sikh Gurdwara Management Committee. Besides being a fantastic vocalist, Bhai Karnail Singh Dhiraj was also a phenomenal tabla player. He accompanied Bhai Mangal Singh Ji on tabla for a few years before forming his own jatha with his brothers. He is an expert in many angs of Kirtan such as Gurmat Sangeet, Shastri Sangeet, Semi classical and light Kirtan as well. By spending many years with Bhai Mangal Singh Ji, he also came to learn many Puratan compositions of Bhai Santa Singh Ji. After forming his jatha, he traveled extensively and visited countries such as Singapore, Thailand, Canada and more before permanently settling in USA.  The information above was narrated to me by Sahib Singh Bakshi. If anyone has more recordings or photos of Bhai Karnail Singh Dhiraj to share, please contact us."
